  Contreras for fix.

*msn-pecan-0.1.0_rc1 (19 Jul 2009)

  19 Jul 2009; Bernard Cafarelli <voyageur@gentoo.org>
  +msn-pecan-0.1.0_rc1.ebuild:
  Version bump, timeout issues fixed, offline messages sending support (and
  better receiving support), crash fixes, performance improvements and code
  reorganization

*msn-pecan-0.0.19 (19 Jul 2009)

  19 Jul 2009; Bernard Cafarelli <voyageur@gentoo.org>
  +msn-pecan-0.0.19.ebuild, +metadata.xml:
  Package move to x11-plugins/msn-pecan

  19 Jul 2009; Bernard Cafarelli <voyageur@gentoo.org>
  -pidgin-msn-pecan-0.0.17.ebuild, -pidgin-msn-pecan-0.0.18.ebuild:
  Remove previous versions

*pidgin-msn-pecan-0.0.19 (16 Jun 2009)

  16 Jun 2009; Bernard Cafarelli <voyageur@gentoo.org>
  -pidgin-msn-pecan-0.0.14.ebuild, -pidgin-msn-pecan-0.0.15.ebuild,
  -pidgin-msn-pecan-0.0.16.ebuild, +pidgin-msn-pecan-0.0.19.ebuild:
  Version bump, bugfixes and support for 'Now Playing' status field. Also
  remove some old versions

*pidgin-msn-pecan-0.0.18 (15 Feb 2009)

  15 Feb 2009; Bernard Cafarelli <voyageur@gentoo.org>
  +pidgin-msn-pecan-0.0.18.ebuild:
  Version bump, bugfixes including personal status messages, adds voice clip
  support, remove Makefile sed for multilib as it's not longer needed and
  breaks things in this version

*pidgin-msn-pecan-0.0.17 (01 Dec 2008)

  01 Dec 2008; Bernard Cafarelli <voyageur@gentoo.org>
  +pidgin-msn-pecan-0.0.17.ebuild:
  Version bump, adds custom emoticon sending support and independent
  personal status messages

*pidgin-msn-pecan-0.0.16 (14 Sep 2008)

